# Files at the monorepo root that don't belong in any Docker build context.
# This applies to all docker builds run with the monorepo root as their context
# (control-panel, external-api, viewer, plugins-api, account-archive). It does
# NOT apply to services whose build context is still apps/<svc>/ — they have
# their own per-service .dockerignore (or none, since their context is small).

.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github
.idea
.vscode
*.iml

# Build artifacts that may exist in service directories
**/build
**/target
**/.gradle
**/node_modules
**/dist

# Test / coverage outputs
**/coverage
**/.nyc_output
**/jacoco

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*~

# Workspace + planning docs are reference, not buildable code
docs/
README.md
*.md

# Operator scripts that aren't relevant inside any build
ops/dev-up.sh
ops/dev-nginx.conf
ops/.env.dev
ops/.env.dev.example
baseline-*/

# Other apps shouldn't bleed into one app's build
# (Each Dockerfile selectively COPYs apps/<its-own-svc>/. and libs/schema/.)
# We don't blanket-ignore apps/ because Dockerfiles need access to their own
# subdir; the per-Dockerfile COPY paths handle the scoping.
